				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-008_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_lauscher_jiri">Jiří Lauscher</persName>, born <date when="1901-09-14">14. 9. 1901</date> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName>, resident in <placeName
							ref="https://www.geonames.org/3064268/terezin.html">Theresienstadt</placeName>.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">Schools</term>: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">village</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134"
							type="subject">town</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">business</term> continuing.</p>
					<p>Trained in the office of the ironworks and rolling mill <date when="1915">1915</date>-<date when="1920">1920</date>.</p>
					<p>In <date when="1920">1920</date>, I travelled to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">United</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">States</placeName> to do a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-913" type="subject">Hachshara</term> at a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-932"
							type="subject">fruit farm</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/11071615/southern-california.html">California</placeName>. In order to get used to the conditions there, I first stayed with some <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
							type="subject">relatives</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/5128581/new-york-city.html">New</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/5128581/new-york-city.html">York</placeName>. I was homesick and I didn’t want to go through the same trouble in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Eretz</placeName>, and so I returned to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/6255148/europe.html">Europe</placeName> and enrolled in the 1st <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-920" type="subject">craft</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-920" type="subject">kibbutz</term> of the <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czechoslovak</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">HeHalutz</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3069011/olomouc.html">Olomouc</placeName> as a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject"
							>cooper</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">carpenter</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3068501/pavlovice-u-prerova.html">Pavlovice</placeName> (<term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">distillery</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">yeast plant</term>). After <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">working</term> for a year, I was sent to Merkas <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">HeHalutz</term>, where I <q><term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">served</term></q> my mandatory year, organized the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">employment</term> office and put together travel packs for
						chalutzim for their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-866" type="subject">aliyah</term>. After working for a year for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">HeHalutz</term>, I was sent to the <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004815">Techelet</orgName>-<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004815">Lavan</orgName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-913" type="subject">retraining</term> summer <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-913" type="subject">camp</term> for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-827"
							type="subject">young</term> (800 people) in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3065398/stara-libava.html">Stará</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3065398/stara-libava.html">Libava</placeName> near Došov by <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3069011/olomouc.html">Olomouc</placeName>, where, as a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057"
							type="subject">cooper</term> with several <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-913" type="subject">retrained</term> chaverim, I made <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">pallets</term>, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">kitchen</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">equipment</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">latrines</term>, etc., and later I was a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">rations master</term> and a technical <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">worker</term>.</p>
					<p>After leaving <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">Merkas</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">HeHalutz</term> was no more, because the chaverim had gone to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Eretz</placeName>, and so we took the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">working</term> chalucim vaad to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070328/moravska-ostrava.html">Mor</placeName>. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070328/moravska-ostrava.html"
							>Ostrava</placeName>, where there was also a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-920" type="subject">craft</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-920" type="subject">kibbutz</term>. I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> in <persName ref="#ehri_dc_pilar_ferdinand">Ferd. Pilař</persName>’s workshop in
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3071025/marianske-hory.html">Mar</placeName>. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3071025/marianske-hory.html">Hory</placeName>, and in the evenings in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871"
							type="subject">HeHalutz</term>. From <date when="1924-09">September 1924</date> to <date when="1925-01">January 1925</date>. I was then sent to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName>, where the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">HeHalutz</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-932" type="subject">gardening</term> group was struggling. A chaver and I were tasked with providing them with a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">livelihood</term>,
						which we managed to do with the help of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">Zionist</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-871" type="subject">leadership</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070328/moravska-ostrava.html">Mor</placeName>. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070328/moravska-ostrava.html"
							>Ostrava</placeName> (Dr. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/terezin-victims-person-iti-1496899" type="victim">Kahn</persName>). In <date when="1925-03">March, 1925</date>, I was urgently sent to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Eretz</placeName>, because there weren’t enough people.</p>
					<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Eretz</placeName>, I immediately began constructing <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">homes</term> in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/295221/-en-gannim.html">En</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/295221/-en-gannim.html">Ganim</placeName>, where we were temporarily stationed. After a short while, I was assigned to the first group in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Emek</placeName>, where our
						group’s hityashvut was supposed to be prepared in cooperation with the first group of <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-328">Hashomer</orgName>
						<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-328">Hatzair</orgName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. After a promising beginning in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/295740/afula.html"
							>Afula</placeName> (<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Israel</placeName>), the crisis and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">unemployment</term> of <date when="1926">1926</date> hit, and so
						we took down the tents and found <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294801/haifa.html">Haifa</placeName> building on <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/294579/mount-carmel.html">Carmel</placeName> and later draining in Mifraz <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/295721/acre.html">Acre</placeName>. In <date when="1927">1927</date>, the Achva group, which partially broke up, joined with the
						hityashvut in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/293640/sarid.html">Sarid</placeName>.</p>
					<p>There, I built new and inspired by <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/295221/-en-gannim.html">Ein Ganim</placeName><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">houses</term>. We soon started working on the construction of a large <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">cowshed</term>, several chicken coops, a hatchery, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-315" type="subject">children’s</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-315" type="subject">home</term>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1040" type="subject">colony</term>’s system of defense, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-939" type="subject">roads</term>, and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">bore holes</term>. We also took over the buildings in neighboring <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/295004/ginnegar.html">Ginegar</placeName> and later in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Emek</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">HaYarden</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Beth</placeName>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html">Sera</placeName>. Since then, there was enough construction <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> in our own <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1040" type="subject">settlement</term>, and so I remained in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/293640/sarid.html">Sarid</placeName> until <date when="1930">1930</date>. I was the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">head</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">expert</term> for all <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">construction work</term> (although I was still actively <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">working</term>), besides overseeing the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">technician</term> from Hanhala Zionit. After surviving a bad case of
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">tropical</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">tertian</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">malaria</term>, I travelled to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6255148/europe.html">Europe</placeName>, where I remained due to a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term>, without giving up on the possibility of returning. I got a job as the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">head</term> of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">factory</term> that tanned and colored furs in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>. In <date when="1938">1938</date>-<date when="1939">39</date>, I specialized in wooden toys that would be manufactured in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/294640/state-of-israel.html"
							>Eretz</placeName>. But <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-866" type="subject">aliyah</term> could not take place. I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> for 2 years in toy <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">factory</term>, and in the last year as a member of a group of about 20 Jewish people up until I was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject"
							>transported</term>. In <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName>, I was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">cooper</term> and I was occasionally
						ordered to manufacture toys for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>, or rather design and create the models for them, as well as models of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">German</placeName> attack vehicles, etc. I devoted myself to conservation and took a toy-making <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-866" type="subject">course</term> in
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>.</p>
